AU  - Buehlmaier, Matthias M M
AU  - Zechner, Josef
T1  - Financial Media, Price Discovery, and Merger Arbitrage*
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfaa037
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 25
IS  - 4
SP  - 997
EP  - 1046
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Using merger announcements and applying methods from computational linguistics we find strong evidence that stock prices underreact to information in financial media. A one standard deviation increase in the media-implied probability of merger completion increases the subsequent 12-day return of a long-short merger strategy by 1.2 percentage points. Filtering out the 28% of announced deals with the lowest media-implied completion probability increases the annualized alpha from merger arbitrage by 9.3 percentage points. Our results are particularly pronounced when high-yield spreads are large and on days when only few merger deals are announced.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfaa037
ER  - 



